WEBVTT

00:01.692 --> 00:04.326
(Finch)
We are being watched.

00:04.328 --> 00:06.494
The government
has a secret system--

00:06.496 --> 00:10.765
a Machine that spies on you
every hour of every day.

00:10.767 --> 00:13.501
I designed the Machine
to detect acts of terror,

00:13.503 --> 00:15.270
but it sees everything...

00:15.272 --> 00:18.740
Violent crimes
involving ordinary people.

00:18.742 --> 00:21.743
The government considers
these people irrelevant.

00:21.745 --> 00:23.678
We don't.

00:23.680 --> 00:28.383
Hunted by the authorities,
we work in secret.

00:28.385 --> 00:30.185
You will never find us.

00:30.187 --> 00:32.320
But victim or perpetrator,

00:32.322 --> 00:35.557
if your number's up,
we'll find you.

00:35.558 --> 00:38.416
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

00:40.931 --> 00:43.331
[dramatic music]

00:43.333 --> 00:44.599
(Reese)
Pick it up, Finch.

00:44.601 --> 00:46.034
It's about time.

00:46.036 --> 00:47.369
(Finch) Is this really
why I was summoned

00:47.371 --> 00:49.170
first thing in the morning?

00:49.172 --> 00:50.772
(Reese)
Beats a cup of coffee.

00:50.774 --> 00:53.508
Who knows?
You might even enjoy it.

00:53.510 --> 00:56.077
While I appreciate the utility
of a firearm, Mr. Reese,

00:56.079 --> 00:58.580
I don't see the pleasure
in firing lead projectiles

00:58.582 --> 01:00.682
at inanimate objects.

01:00.684 --> 01:03.051
This isn't pleasure,
it's business.

01:03.053 --> 01:04.852
You've had some close calls
recently.

01:04.855 --> 01:08.757
♪ ♪

01:08.759 --> 01:11.126
Think of it as a machine.

01:11.128 --> 01:13.561
You like machines,
right, Finch?

01:13.563 --> 01:15.797
[gunshots ringing
and glass shattering]

01:15.799 --> 01:17.966
Or maybe a hun more your style.

01:17.968 --> 01:22.537
♪ ♪

01:22.539 --> 01:25.874
I won't be around forever.

01:25.876 --> 01:29.210
I just need to know you can
protect yourself once I'm gone.

01:29.212 --> 01:31.913
When the time comes
for me to pick up a firearm,

01:31.915 --> 01:34.416
all will truly be lost.

01:34.418 --> 01:38.987
[phone ringing]

01:38.989 --> 01:42.885
♪ ♪

01:45.037 --> 01:47.960
_

01:47.963 --> 01:48.897
[phone line trilling]

01:48.899 --> 01:51.199
♪ ♪

01:51.201 --> 01:52.734
[phone vibrating]

01:52.736 --> 01:53.935
(Kelly)
Boss?

01:53.937 --> 01:54.970
Mr. Khan?

01:54.972 --> 01:56.738
[footsteps approaching]

01:56.740 --> 01:58.406
[phone vibrating]

01:58.408 --> 02:01.576
Why haven't you picked up
your phone, Saul?

02:01.578 --> 02:03.178
Saul, wake up!

02:03.180 --> 02:05.347
- Turn on the TV.
- What? What are you--

02:05.349 --> 02:08.883
(male reporter) If you are just joining
us, an update now to our top story.

02:08.886 --> 02:10.352
- Company officials have yet...
- You've been hacked.

02:10.354 --> 02:12.354
...to release an official statement

02:12.356 --> 02:16.024
even as hundreds of private
documents have been made public.

02:16.026 --> 02:17.826
- What did they get?
- Corporate accounts,

02:17.828 --> 02:20.295
financial records,
salary, bonuses.

02:20.297 --> 02:22.264
Every email you ever sent.

02:22.266 --> 02:24.599
How bad?

02:24.601 --> 02:26.935
The leak proves you were
embezzling company funds.

02:26.937 --> 02:29.404
What?
That's-- that's ridiculous.

02:29.406 --> 02:30.639
The board is meeting
in an hour.

02:30.641 --> 02:32.007
They're moving to fire you.

02:32.009 --> 02:34.609
Okay, call Mark.

02:34.611 --> 02:37.579
Tell him to stall.

02:37.581 --> 02:38.713
What networks
are covering this?

02:38.715 --> 02:40.048
- All of them.
- Uh-huh?

02:40.050 --> 02:41.383
Fox News, Huffington,
<i>The Journal.</i>

02:41.385 --> 02:44.352
CNN already
has a hashtag for it.

02:44.354 --> 02:45.553
TMZ just posted
how much you lost

02:45.555 --> 02:46.621
in the stock market
flash crash.

02:46.623 --> 02:48.723
- [doorbell rings]
- Wow.

02:48.725 --> 02:50.392
[intercom beeps]

02:50.394 --> 02:52.327
(man over intercom)
Internal Revenue Service.

02:52.329 --> 02:55.297
We need to talk
to Sulaiman Khan.

02:55.299 --> 02:56.798
What do I do?

02:56.800 --> 02:57.999
Buy me some time.

02:58.001 --> 02:59.401
I got to get to this meeting.

02:59.403 --> 03:00.302
And I got to fix this.

03:00.304 --> 03:08.576
♪ ♪

03:13.583 --> 03:15.884
- [camera clicking]
- Got eyes on him, Finch.

03:15.886 --> 03:17.986
(Finch)
As do I.

03:17.988 --> 03:22.691
Out new number has become
infamous overnight.

03:22.693 --> 03:27.996
Meet Sulaiman Khan, CEO of
Castellum Security Incorporated,

03:27.998 --> 03:32.367
a pioneer in computer
antivirus software.

03:32.369 --> 03:35.370
What started out in his garage,
has now grown

03:35.372 --> 03:37.505
to be the leading security
software company

03:37.507 --> 03:39.174
in the entire world.

03:39.176 --> 03:41.609
Judging from his home,
it's made him a few dollars.

03:41.611 --> 03:43.311
(Finch)
More like billions.

03:43.313 --> 03:48.416
Although, Mr. Khan's personal
finances took a huge hit

03:48.418 --> 03:50.318
in the stock market flash crash.

03:50.320 --> 03:52.787
He's lucky his company
is still standing.

03:52.789 --> 03:56.791
Khan's antiviral software
comes pre-installed in 86%

03:56.793 --> 03:59.294
of the network devices
now sold around the globe.

03:59.296 --> 04:01.363
Entire divisions
within the government

04:01.365 --> 04:03.498
are using versions
of his product,

04:03.500 --> 04:06.234
which makes him a prime target
for hackers.

04:06.236 --> 04:08.670
They all want to take a shot
at the sheriff.

04:08.672 --> 04:10.905
It'd be quite a feat
to infiltrate the man

04:10.907 --> 04:13.108
who built the ultimate firewall.

04:13.110 --> 04:15.443
Explains why I haven't been able
to bluejack him.

04:15.445 --> 04:19.014
It's extremely difficult
to access him remotely.

04:19.016 --> 04:20.781
His security measures
are rigorous

04:20.784 --> 04:22.384
and virtually unassailable.

04:22.386 --> 04:25.520
Only the paranoid survive,
right, Finch?

04:25.522 --> 04:29.491
It's not paranoia
if they're really after you.

04:29.493 --> 04:31.526
Whoever got to him is very good.

04:31.528 --> 04:33.962
♪ ♪

04:33.964 --> 04:35.430
[camera clicks]

04:35.432 --> 04:36.865
Just so we're not flying
completely blind,

04:36.867 --> 04:38.666
I went ahead
and bluejacked his assistant.

04:38.668 --> 04:41.736
I'll attempt to access everyone
in his inner circle.

04:41.738 --> 04:43.104
You stay on the number.

04:43.106 --> 04:44.639
[car alarm beeping ]

04:44.641 --> 04:46.141
Oh, he's not going anywhere,
Finch.

04:46.143 --> 04:47.642
His key no longer works.

04:47.644 --> 04:49.210
(Finch) The hackers may
have accessed his car

04:49.212 --> 04:50.645
and voided the smart key.

04:50.647 --> 04:53.415
They could just be getting
warmed up.

04:53.417 --> 04:55.350
He's sure determined
to get to his meeting.

04:55.352 --> 04:56.851
He's about to do something rash.

04:56.853 --> 04:58.753
I need to gather more info
about this

04:58.755 --> 05:02.057
advanced persistent threat,
see how he was doxxed.

05:02.059 --> 05:03.858
Can't you get Root on this?

05:03.860 --> 05:07.796
Sorry. Ms. Groves and I are not
on the best of terms.

05:07.798 --> 05:09.764
(Reese)
Better kiss and make up, Finch.

05:09.766 --> 05:11.232
We could use her on this one.

05:11.234 --> 05:13.268
♪ ♪

05:16.006 --> 05:18.073
(man)
There you are, ma'am.

05:18.075 --> 05:20.508
[mysterious music]

05:20.510 --> 05:22.010
(woman)
This way.

05:22.012 --> 05:25.747
♪ ♪

05:25.749 --> 05:27.048
Here you are.

05:27.050 --> 05:28.750
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

05:28.752 --> 05:29.984
(man)
How are you?

05:29.986 --> 05:31.853
Are you sure
the item is intact?

05:31.855 --> 05:34.722
Please, it's custom made
with a built-in GPS tracker.

05:34.724 --> 05:35.890
I've got a guy.

05:35.892 --> 05:36.958
Could drop this
from an airplane,

05:36.960 --> 05:38.993
not even a dent.

05:38.995 --> 05:41.496
[phone beeping]

05:41.498 --> 05:43.298
[static on camera]

05:43.300 --> 05:44.866
Another mimosa, Miss?

05:44.868 --> 05:46.267
You may want to sit down.

05:46.269 --> 05:49.204
[suspenseful music]

05:49.206 --> 05:57.479
♪ ♪

05:58.715 --> 06:01.649
[bodies thudding]

06:01.651 --> 06:09.924
♪ ♪

06:14.464 --> 06:16.131
Thank you.

06:16.133 --> 06:20.001
♪ ♪

06:23.740 --> 06:26.674
[mysterious music]

06:26.676 --> 06:33.281
♪ ♪

06:33.283 --> 06:35.316
(Finch) The board meeting
is well underway.

06:35.318 --> 06:37.218
Time is running out
if he plans to intervene.

06:37.220 --> 06:39.654
[phone rings]

06:39.656 --> 06:41.422
♪ ♪

06:41.424 --> 06:42.891
Hello?

06:42.893 --> 06:44.993
Finch, I can't get close enough
to overhear

06:44.995 --> 06:46.928
his side of the conversation.

06:46.930 --> 06:48.863
Taken care of.

06:48.865 --> 06:51.866
While Mr. Khan may take
extreme security measures,

06:51.868 --> 06:53.501
his wife does not.

06:53.503 --> 06:55.036
(Khan on phone) Linda, this
is not a good time, okay?

06:55.038 --> 06:56.571
I'm walking into a meeting.

06:56.573 --> 06:57.572
(Linda)
You disgust me.

06:57.574 --> 06:59.307
You swore you deleted them.

06:59.309 --> 07:00.475
(Khan)
Deleted what?

07:00.477 --> 07:02.911
The pictures from Cabo.

07:02.913 --> 07:04.245
Oh, no.

07:04.247 --> 07:07.448
Oh, my.

07:07.450 --> 07:08.716
You gave me your word.

07:08.718 --> 07:10.618
I did, okay?
It's not my fault.

07:10.620 --> 07:12.954
(Finch) Credit card records
from the leak show

07:12.956 --> 07:15.490
that Linda has been staying
in a hotel for the last month.

07:15.492 --> 07:17.258
They're seeing
a marriage counselor.

07:17.260 --> 07:18.826
(Linda)
They are everywhere.

07:18.828 --> 07:20.728
All of my coworkers have
probably seen them by now.

07:20.730 --> 07:23.364
I will never be able to look
my boss in the face again.

07:23.366 --> 07:25.600
This will follow me forever.

07:25.602 --> 07:27.702
Someone is trying to ruin me.

07:27.704 --> 07:29.571
Linda, you have to--
[phone beeps]

07:29.573 --> 07:32.707
♪ ♪

07:32.709 --> 07:35.577
(Nicassio) Khan embezzled millions
upon millions of dollars--

07:35.579 --> 07:36.911
(Finch)
Mr. Reese?

07:36.913 --> 07:38.546
Don't worry, Finch.

07:38.548 --> 07:40.815
We still have eyes and ears
in the meeting.

07:40.817 --> 07:43.384
- Did you bug him?
- One better.

07:43.386 --> 07:48.122
(Nicassio) If anything, this
hack, it was a sign from God.

07:48.124 --> 07:51.659
Well, this turnaround guy
sure is sanctimonious.

07:51.661 --> 07:52.961
Too bad you can't be here

07:52.963 --> 07:54.729
to stimulate the conversation,
John.

07:54.731 --> 07:57.332
(Reese) I'm not much
of a public speaker.

07:57.334 --> 07:59.133
But I promise
to make an appearance

07:59.135 --> 08:01.069
if things get exciting.

08:01.071 --> 08:04.872
Things always get exciting
when you're here.

08:04.874 --> 08:06.474
Khan has to go.

08:06.476 --> 08:10.078
This company is far too
profitable to let him sink it.

08:10.080 --> 08:11.713
That's why the board
brought me in last month.

08:11.715 --> 08:14.916
(Reese) Khan's on his
way into the meeting.

08:14.918 --> 08:18.386
Okay, I know it's bad,
but come on.

08:18.388 --> 08:20.488
It's not Zoe Morgan bad.
Right?

08:20.490 --> 08:22.824
Well, if the board hired me,

08:22.826 --> 08:25.293
it seems it's worse
than you thought.

08:25.295 --> 08:27.795
It's the first meeting
I've ever seen him show up to.

08:27.797 --> 08:29.130
It's also your last.

08:29.132 --> 08:30.565
Okay.
They're never going to agree.

08:30.567 --> 08:32.667
- Now listen--
- The vote was unanimous.

08:32.669 --> 08:34.969
You're out.

08:34.971 --> 08:37.705
(Khan) Hey, come on. Dean, Gus?

08:37.707 --> 08:39.841
Okay.

08:39.842 --> 08:41.943
Even you, Mark?

08:41.945 --> 08:44.212
Buddy, I was best man
at your wedding, for God's sake.

08:44.214 --> 08:46.047
I mean, you and I
came up together,

08:46.049 --> 08:47.181
four guys in the garage.

08:47.183 --> 08:48.883
What did your email say again?

08:48.885 --> 08:51.686
Uh, Mark Lee has the backbone
of a dead jellyfish.

08:51.688 --> 08:53.187
Yeah, that was it.

08:53.189 --> 08:55.123
Yes, I wrote that email.

08:55.125 --> 08:56.891
I was angry.
I'm sorry.

08:56.893 --> 08:58.626
Obviously,
I don't feel that way.

08:58.628 --> 09:00.128
Look, there's a lot of things

09:00.130 --> 09:02.530
I've written in private emails
that I regret.

09:02.532 --> 09:04.966
It's true.
I'm embarrassed.

09:04.968 --> 09:07.435
I said it.

09:07.437 --> 09:10.805
But embezzling money
from this company?

09:10.807 --> 09:12.540
No.

09:12.542 --> 09:14.776
That is an outright lie.

09:14.778 --> 09:17.312
And it is clear
that I'm being set up.

09:17.314 --> 09:20.982
Well, three teams of analysts
say otherwise.

09:20.984 --> 09:22.917
The company needs
to distance itself.

09:22.919 --> 09:24.118
It's my company.

09:24.120 --> 09:25.420
Not anymore.

09:25.422 --> 09:28.122
[laughs]

09:28.124 --> 09:31.192
You've been trying to steal
my research since day one.

09:31.194 --> 09:32.860
You hear that, Finch?

09:32.862 --> 09:36.030
Judging by the hard-coded paths
in the malware,

09:36.032 --> 09:37.999
whoever's behind this hack
had an extensive knowledge

09:38.001 --> 09:41.002
of the company's
internal architecture.

09:41.004 --> 09:43.204
It appears that the threat
came from within.

09:43.206 --> 09:44.772
You got bored
with the core software.

09:44.774 --> 09:47.041
I created the core software.

09:47.043 --> 09:48.810
Do you have any idea
who you're talking to?

09:48.812 --> 09:51.045
Hmm?
I'm an innovator.

09:51.047 --> 09:54.082
You are nothing more than
a glorified accountant.

09:54.084 --> 09:55.583
You're not that guy anymore.

09:55.585 --> 09:57.085
You lost focus.

09:57.087 --> 10:00.722
Draining resources
for secret side projects,

10:00.724 --> 10:02.557
and driving this company
to bankruptcy.

10:02.559 --> 10:05.259
No.
Towards the future.

10:05.261 --> 10:09.130
Listen, can any of you think
beyond next quarter's numbers?

10:09.132 --> 10:12.934
To stay relevant,
we need vision.

10:12.936 --> 10:14.202
Since this guy came along,

10:14.204 --> 10:16.904
the software has become bloated,
slow.

10:16.906 --> 10:19.640
Frankly, the last update
that we had took us backwards

10:19.642 --> 10:22.310
in terms of design
and efficiency.

10:22.312 --> 10:24.979
But the work I'm doing in
digital immunization technology

10:24.981 --> 10:27.215
is gonna take this company
to another level.

10:27.217 --> 10:32.687
Imagine a chip that can tell you
when your vaccine is outdated.

10:32.689 --> 10:34.288
Biotech.

10:34.290 --> 10:37.024
That's what you blew
$400 million on?

10:37.026 --> 10:38.593
No, no, no--
whoa, whoa.

10:38.595 --> 10:40.595
Four-- Where did you get
that figure?

10:40.597 --> 10:42.296
From your financial records.

10:42.298 --> 10:44.232
You lost all your money
in the crash,

10:44.234 --> 10:46.768
so you stole from this company
to fund your research.

10:46.770 --> 10:49.971
I have not stolen a cent.

10:49.973 --> 10:53.074
I am being set up
and we both know

10:53.076 --> 10:54.342
who is behind it.

10:54.344 --> 10:56.277
You sure this isn't all
in your head?

10:56.279 --> 10:57.945
I didn't want to bring this up,

10:57.947 --> 11:00.148
but your medical records
were made public,

11:00.150 --> 11:01.816
and the last thing
this company needs

11:01.818 --> 11:03.885
is a bipolar CEO.

11:03.887 --> 11:06.120
Hey, hey,
that is privileged inform--

11:06.122 --> 11:08.823
Look, I...
I got it under control.

11:08.825 --> 11:10.658
I take the meds, okay?

11:10.660 --> 11:12.493
Well, judging
from your behavior,

11:12.495 --> 11:14.862
maybe it's about time
to up the dosage.

11:14.864 --> 11:17.565
Escort Mr. Khan
out of the building.

11:17.567 --> 11:19.133
- Guys...
- And take his ID badge.

11:19.135 --> 11:20.768
Come on.
Hey, this is--

11:20.770 --> 11:21.969
Get off of me!

11:21.971 --> 11:23.638
You get away!

11:23.640 --> 11:24.839
This is not over!

11:24.841 --> 11:26.841
[glass shattering]

11:26.843 --> 11:28.476
(Finch)
If Khan's truly unstable,

11:28.478 --> 11:30.611
there's no telling
how he'll react.

11:30.613 --> 11:33.214
Finch, this takeover
just got hostile.

11:35.000 --> 11:41.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

11:48.349 --> 11:50.082
Hey. Hey, hey, hey.
Come on.

11:50.084 --> 11:52.952
Come on.
You can't just take my stuff.

11:52.954 --> 11:53.919
Actually, we can.

11:53.921 --> 11:59.625
♪ ♪

11:59.627 --> 12:01.560
[phone beeping]

12:01.562 --> 12:02.761
[phone line trilling]

12:02.763 --> 12:04.430
(Mandy on phone)
Waxman Law Offices.

12:04.432 --> 12:06.398
- Where can I direct your call?
- It's Saul Khan.

12:06.400 --> 12:08.200
(Khan)
Can you tell Ira it's urgent?

12:08.202 --> 12:09.401
(Mandy) Mr. Waxman is
currently unavailable.

12:09.403 --> 12:11.136
Can I take a message?

12:11.138 --> 12:12.571
(Khan) Mandy, would you please
just put him on the phone?

12:12.573 --> 12:13.939
(Mandy)
I'm sorry to inform you, sir,

12:13.941 --> 12:15.641
but the firm has dropped you
as a client,

12:15.643 --> 12:16.775
effective immediately.

12:16.777 --> 12:18.477
[click and dial tone]

12:18.479 --> 12:19.979
[phone beeps]

12:19.981 --> 12:21.280
Linda.

12:21.282 --> 12:22.815
- The IRS is my parents' house.
- Okay.

12:22.817 --> 12:24.583
Something about
civil assets forfeiture.

12:24.585 --> 12:25.951
Okay, I swear,
I am being set up.

12:25.953 --> 12:27.619
(Linda)
No. You got caught.

12:27.621 --> 12:28.687
And you deserve everything
that's coming to you.

12:28.689 --> 12:30.289
I can fix this.
Okay?

12:30.291 --> 12:34.126
Even you can't put the pieces
back together now.

12:34.128 --> 12:36.428
(Zoe) Are you sure you're ready
for a relationship, John?

12:36.430 --> 12:38.964
She's not gonna hang around
forever.

12:38.966 --> 12:41.800
Those therapist types,
they want to settle down.

12:41.802 --> 12:44.770
Are you spying on me, Zoe?

12:44.772 --> 12:48.741
You know, I never figured you
with a redhead.

12:48.743 --> 12:50.809
♪ ♪

12:50.811 --> 12:52.177
Jealous?

12:52.179 --> 12:55.280
No.
Protective.

12:55.282 --> 12:56.982
I'll be okay.

12:56.984 --> 12:59.985
She's the one
I'm worried about.

12:59.987 --> 13:01.720
You know how this ends.

13:01.722 --> 13:03.922
Let's just focus on the case.

13:03.924 --> 13:06.291
Finch is working
to ID the hacker.

13:06.293 --> 13:09.495
We should check in,
see if he's made any progress.

13:09.497 --> 13:12.698
You find it odd that the hacker
only went after Khan?

13:12.700 --> 13:14.500
Not the rest of the company?

13:14.502 --> 13:16.502
What makes you so sure?

13:16.504 --> 13:19.905
No mention of the accounting
scandal in 2011.

13:19.907 --> 13:21.740
How do you know about that?

13:21.742 --> 13:24.309
I'm the one they hired
to clean up their mess.

13:24.311 --> 13:25.878
When one of the studios
got hacked,

13:25.880 --> 13:27.913
it was like a shotgun blast.

13:27.915 --> 13:29.381
Scatter shot.

13:29.383 --> 13:30.749
Whatever they could hit.

13:30.751 --> 13:34.053
This attack on Khan
is surgical.

13:34.055 --> 13:36.422
Someone wanted to ruin
this guy's life,

13:36.424 --> 13:37.856
not harm the company.

13:37.858 --> 13:39.258
I can name a few board members

13:39.260 --> 13:42.261
who benefit
from Khan being ousted.

13:42.263 --> 13:44.696
Whoever's behind this...

13:44.698 --> 13:47.833
it's personal.

13:47.835 --> 13:55.140
♪ ♪

14:00.815 --> 14:04.049
♪ ♪

14:04.051 --> 14:05.684
Thought you'd be gone too.

14:05.686 --> 14:08.320
Sure said some terrible things
about you over the years.

14:08.322 --> 14:09.621
You've said worse to my face.

14:09.623 --> 14:12.858
♪ ♪

14:12.860 --> 14:15.127
I didn't take the job
'cause you were a nice guy.

14:15.129 --> 14:16.695
This is all my fault.

14:16.697 --> 14:18.030
I'm so focused
on that bio-chip

14:18.032 --> 14:20.732
that I left myself open
to an attack.

14:20.734 --> 14:22.468
So fight back.

14:22.470 --> 14:23.869
Isn't that why you started
the company in the first place?

14:23.871 --> 14:26.238
♪ ♪

14:26.240 --> 14:29.241
Yes.
It is.

14:29.243 --> 14:30.309
Did you get the other thing?

14:30.311 --> 14:32.911
♪ ♪

14:32.913 --> 14:36.615
How do you know he'll show up?

14:36.617 --> 14:39.118
Because Mark is predictable.

14:39.120 --> 14:40.752
If there's one thing
I can count on,

14:40.754 --> 14:43.922
he will not pass up
an opportunity to see me squirm.

14:43.924 --> 14:45.257
Is this registered?

14:45.259 --> 14:46.558
That would've taken
a lot more time

14:46.560 --> 14:47.893
and probably defeated
the purpose.

14:47.895 --> 14:49.995
♪ ♪

14:49.997 --> 14:51.630
I'm guessing.

14:51.632 --> 14:52.564
Thank you.

14:52.566 --> 14:56.101
♪ ♪

14:56.103 --> 14:57.703
Anytime, boss.

14:57.705 --> 15:01.006
♪ ♪

15:04.211 --> 15:07.980
(man) The tracker says the
case is on this floor.

15:07.982 --> 15:11.650
[tracker beeping]

15:11.652 --> 15:14.686
[banging]

15:14.688 --> 15:15.988
[grunts]

15:15.990 --> 15:18.857
[suspenseful music]

15:18.859 --> 15:20.359
I know we've had our differences
lately,

15:20.361 --> 15:22.194
but I really miss the days
when you could just

15:22.196 --> 15:23.529
tell me what to do.

15:23.531 --> 15:27.232
Where's the tracker?

15:27.234 --> 15:30.002
All right,
if you won't tell me,

15:30.004 --> 15:33.739
110 volts should fry it.

15:33.741 --> 15:34.873
[electricity crackling]

15:34.875 --> 15:37.876
(man)
I just lost the signal.

15:37.878 --> 15:39.478
(man)
It's got to be in here.

15:39.480 --> 15:42.748
♪ ♪

15:42.750 --> 15:43.882
[grunts]

15:43.884 --> 15:46.818
♪ ♪

15:46.820 --> 15:49.855
Where's the damn case?

15:49.857 --> 15:51.557
Come on.
Let's go.

15:51.559 --> 15:53.892
- [couple whimpering]
- Shh.

15:53.894 --> 15:57.196
- [banging on door]
- Ah!

15:57.198 --> 15:59.565
[gunshots]

15:59.567 --> 16:01.733
[bullets ricocheting]

16:01.735 --> 16:02.834
[gun clicking]

16:02.836 --> 16:03.936
[grunts]

16:03.938 --> 16:06.471
♪ ♪

16:06.473 --> 16:11.009
Could drop it from an airplane,
not even a dent.

16:11.011 --> 16:13.045
♪ ♪

16:15.583 --> 16:18.517
[bluesy rock plays]

16:18.519 --> 16:27.559
♪ ♪

16:27.561 --> 16:30.996
(Reese) Shady part of town.
No cameras.

16:30.998 --> 16:33.465
Khan must have picked this place
for a reason.

16:33.467 --> 16:38.203
(Finch) Khan may have lured his
old friend there to take revenge.

16:38.205 --> 16:39.972
(Reese)
Think Mark's behind the attack?

16:39.974 --> 16:42.874
He's capable, with plenty
to gain by bringing Khan down.

16:42.876 --> 16:45.677
♪ ♪

16:45.679 --> 16:48.714
[mysterious music]

16:48.716 --> 16:51.116
[phone beeping]

16:51.118 --> 16:53.719
♪ ♪

16:53.721 --> 16:54.853
Thanks.

16:54.855 --> 16:57.656
I needed to see you in person.

16:57.658 --> 17:00.926
Hey.
I just bought this.

17:00.928 --> 17:02.194
What the hell, man?

17:02.196 --> 17:04.896
They could be listening to us.

17:04.897 --> 17:06.064
Who?

17:06.066 --> 17:07.866
You know I didn't do it, right?

17:07.867 --> 17:12.037
Mark, we've been friends
for 30 years.

17:12.039 --> 17:14.573
I need you to trust me.

17:14.575 --> 17:16.407
My entire life has gone viral,

17:16.410 --> 17:17.909
and I need to find out why.

17:17.911 --> 17:20.178
There's no grand conspiracy
here.

17:20.180 --> 17:21.546
You got hacked.

17:21.548 --> 17:23.482
Oh, yeah?
Just me?

17:23.483 --> 17:25.751
Hmm?
No one else was touched?

17:25.752 --> 17:27.085
You're the face of the company.

17:27.087 --> 17:29.888
This wasn't about
sending a message.

17:29.890 --> 17:32.924
Why'd you ask
for me here, Saul?

17:32.926 --> 17:34.726
I need you to go
to the meter room.

17:34.728 --> 17:36.528
I'm not risking my job for you.

17:36.530 --> 17:40.432
We created the world's
preeminent antivirus software.

17:40.434 --> 17:42.934
Don't you want to know
how that thing just got gutted?

17:42.936 --> 17:44.970
Hmm?
Isn't it driving you crazy?

17:44.972 --> 17:46.305
'Cause it's eating me alive.

17:46.307 --> 17:49.541
Now please, I need
to see those gauges.

17:49.543 --> 17:53.245
What aren't you telling me?

17:53.247 --> 17:56.248
A few weeks ago, when I was
working on my gene-chip,

17:56.250 --> 17:58.417
the entire facility went dark.

17:58.419 --> 17:59.685
Right?

17:59.687 --> 18:01.620
Now, it turned out
that the accounts

18:01.622 --> 18:03.822
to pay for the power
had been drained.

18:03.824 --> 18:05.090
You know me,
I went down to talk

18:05.092 --> 18:06.625
to the accountant directly.

18:06.627 --> 18:08.327
Turns out that the funds
were used

18:08.329 --> 18:12.464
to pay for a shipment
of 25,000 barrels of diesel.

18:12.466 --> 18:13.865
Come on.

18:13.867 --> 18:17.669
When did our company need
that kind of fuel?

18:17.671 --> 18:19.304
Hey.

18:19.306 --> 18:21.707
The stock market flash crash?

18:21.709 --> 18:23.208
That wasn't just random.

18:23.210 --> 18:26.345
It was targeted at me.

18:26.347 --> 18:28.480
Every equity I had went belly up
within seconds,

18:28.482 --> 18:32.317
except for the shares
that I had in our company.

18:32.319 --> 18:35.320
They didn't want that touched.

18:35.322 --> 18:36.822
Finch, does that check out?

18:36.824 --> 18:40.826
Yes, and those odds
are astronomical.

18:40.828 --> 18:42.494
I intend to find out why.

18:42.496 --> 18:44.796
Who has the ability to control
the stock market, Saul?

18:44.798 --> 18:46.631
There's only one thing
powerful enough

18:46.633 --> 18:48.934
to systematically destroy
Khan's personal

18:48.936 --> 18:50.736
and professional life
this thoroughly.

18:50.738 --> 18:53.572
(Khan)
Well, this is the crazy part.

18:53.574 --> 18:55.874
It's not a human
that's after me.

18:55.876 --> 18:57.476
It's an
Artificial Intelligence.

18:57.478 --> 18:59.111
Samaritan.

18:59.113 --> 19:00.345
(Khan)
It's here.

19:00.347 --> 19:02.647
We always knew
this was possible.

19:02.649 --> 19:03.982
Consider what's happened to me.

19:03.984 --> 19:05.984
Are you really this arrogant? _

19:05.986 --> 19:08.019
(Mark) Is there nothing
that's able to beat you

19:08.021 --> 19:10.522
except
an Artificial Intelligence?

19:10.524 --> 19:12.391
You and I have gone up
against the best.

19:12.393 --> 19:16.461
I'm telling you,
this attack was faster

19:16.463 --> 19:20.065
and more dangerous
than anything I have ever seen.

19:20.067 --> 19:23.101
Let me explore
the possible two options.

19:23.103 --> 19:24.970
The first, you're nuts.

19:24.972 --> 19:27.005
The second, you're right.

19:27.007 --> 19:28.774
There's a Super Intelligence
after you

19:28.776 --> 19:31.276
and every move you make
is being watched.

19:31.278 --> 19:35.814
Either way, best I stay as far
away from you as possible.

19:35.816 --> 19:40.719
I need you to check
those meters.

19:40.721 --> 19:41.987
Get off of me.

19:41.989 --> 19:48.026
♪ ♪

19:48.028 --> 19:52.998
Finch, Khan lured Mark here
to steal his employee ID badge.

19:53.000 --> 19:54.699
I've got to stop him.

19:54.701 --> 19:56.835
If this is Samaritan,
he's got a target on his back.

19:56.837 --> 19:59.337
You can't afford to get caught
in the crosshairs again.

19:59.339 --> 20:01.506
Yeah, well, he's gonna get
himself killed.

20:01.508 --> 20:03.809
There's no way to keep
the victim safe

20:03.811 --> 20:05.811
if the perpetrator is Samaritan.

20:05.813 --> 20:10.515
♪ ♪

20:13.821 --> 20:16.755
[mysterious music]

20:16.757 --> 20:18.123
♪ ♪

20:18.125 --> 20:19.491
[door beeps]

20:19.493 --> 20:22.260
♪ ♪

20:22.262 --> 20:25.163
[drill whirring]

20:25.165 --> 20:28.099
♪ ♪

20:28.101 --> 20:30.088
[alarm beeping] _

20:32.105 --> 20:35.073
[drill whirring]

20:35.075 --> 20:38.109
[suspenseful music]

20:38.111 --> 20:40.111
[grunts]

20:40.113 --> 20:42.614
[body thuds]

20:42.616 --> 20:50.889
♪ ♪

20:56.964 --> 20:58.163
[camera clicking]

20:58.165 --> 20:59.130
(Finch)
What's he looking for?

20:59.132 --> 21:02.901
♪ ♪

21:02.903 --> 21:05.637
If that system is drawing
that much power,

21:05.639 --> 21:08.073
it's doing a lot more
than just scanning for viruses.

21:08.075 --> 21:10.208
We need to find out
what he knows.

21:10.210 --> 21:11.643
I'm making a move, Finch.

21:11.645 --> 21:13.979
(Finch) No. NYPD has
arrived on the premises.

21:13.981 --> 21:16.581
Detective Riley
has no business being there.

21:16.583 --> 21:18.783
Samaritan will see through
your cover instantly,

21:18.785 --> 21:20.752
endangering you
and everyone you're close to.

21:20.754 --> 21:24.990
♪ ♪

21:24.992 --> 21:26.324
- NYPD!
- Get your hands behind

21:26.326 --> 21:27.325
your back.

21:27.327 --> 21:29.060
Up against the wall.

21:29.062 --> 21:32.097
♪ ♪

21:32.099 --> 21:33.798
He's clean.

21:33.800 --> 21:36.334
We just lost the number, Finch.

21:51.533 --> 21:54.668
I believe an exception
to the no-smoking policy

21:54.670 --> 21:55.969
is in order here.

21:55.971 --> 21:58.405
Named after
the Nepalese warriors

21:58.407 --> 22:01.208
whose undying bravery
made a lasting impression

22:01.210 --> 22:03.577
on the British soldiers.

22:03.579 --> 22:06.546
Over $50,000 a box.

22:06.548 --> 22:08.982
Extravagant, even for you.

22:08.984 --> 22:11.852
I believe a small celebration
is called for.

22:11.854 --> 22:14.855
Our online search is drawing
to a close,

22:14.857 --> 22:18.191
with our quarry in sight.

22:18.193 --> 22:20.193
Khan is still a loose end.

22:20.195 --> 22:21.428
Mm.

22:21.430 --> 22:23.830
Unfortunate inconvenience.

22:23.832 --> 22:27.834
His insatiable curiosity
will be the death of him.

22:27.836 --> 22:31.738
He's forced our hand.

22:31.740 --> 22:33.440
Why haven't I been activated?

22:33.442 --> 22:35.942
Samaritan wanted to handle
this matter personally.

22:35.944 --> 22:38.678
Then let me take care
of Ms. Groves.

22:38.680 --> 22:40.881
You've already had your chances
with her.

22:40.883 --> 22:43.083
Then let's leave nothing
to chance.

22:43.085 --> 22:45.118
As my directive.

22:45.120 --> 22:46.353
It's time for her to go.

22:46.355 --> 22:48.789
I suppose you're right.

22:48.791 --> 22:50.557
Shame really.

22:50.559 --> 22:52.592
If only because
she had the misfortune

22:52.594 --> 22:55.128
of honoring the wrong god.

22:55.130 --> 22:58.064
[suspenseful music]

22:58.066 --> 23:00.267
♪ ♪

23:02.971 --> 23:04.504
(Fusco)
That's impossible.

23:04.506 --> 23:06.072
What's that guy doing
over there?

23:06.074 --> 23:09.009
Guy was picked up
for a simple trespassing.

23:09.011 --> 23:12.078
I don't care
what the computer says.

23:15.117 --> 23:18.418
Khan was sent to Rikers.

23:18.420 --> 23:20.921
He was arrested 20 minutes ago.

23:20.923 --> 23:22.956
There's no way he got processed
that fast.

23:22.958 --> 23:24.457
Sounds like somebody's got it in
for this guy.

23:24.459 --> 23:25.926
Well, we got to get him out.

23:25.928 --> 23:28.261
Good luck. Captain wants me
on that other case.

23:28.263 --> 23:30.030
That guy's already dead.
This one's about to be.

23:30.032 --> 23:32.732
Come on, Lionel.

23:32.734 --> 23:34.434
Should have intervened
when I had the chance, Finch.

23:34.436 --> 23:36.002
Khan is being railroaded.

23:36.004 --> 23:37.637
(Finch) Any attempt to
hack the police database

23:37.639 --> 23:39.439
may alert Samaritan
to my presence.

23:39.441 --> 23:40.974
Samaritan is trying
to bury this guy

23:40.976 --> 23:42.576
in a deep, dark hole forever.

23:42.578 --> 23:45.245
And his insatiable need
to confirm that fact

23:45.247 --> 23:46.246
will be the death of him.

23:46.248 --> 23:54.120
♪ ♪

23:54.122 --> 23:55.488
I know my rights.
I get a phone call.

23:55.490 --> 23:57.123
I didn't get my phone call.

23:57.125 --> 23:58.792
Says here you already got it.

23:58.794 --> 24:00.727
What?
No, I didn't.

24:00.729 --> 24:02.362
What are you talking--
I didn't get a phone call.

24:02.364 --> 24:03.563
I didn't get a phone call!

24:03.565 --> 24:05.465
Hey, who did I call?
Okay?

24:05.467 --> 24:06.933
I didn't get a phone call.

24:06.935 --> 24:08.401
What are you--

24:08.403 --> 24:10.070
- [camera clicks]
- Just listen to me, okay?

24:10.072 --> 24:11.972
Where are you taking me?
Where am I going right now?

24:11.974 --> 24:13.506
What are the charges against me,
huh?

24:13.508 --> 24:15.141
If he asks for Officer Brown--

24:15.143 --> 24:17.177
That's my witness
in a joint case with the Feds.

24:17.179 --> 24:18.411
- So where are the Feds?
- Start typing.

24:18.413 --> 24:19.746
I better be walking out of here

24:19.748 --> 24:20.947
with Khan in the next
five minutes.

24:20.949 --> 24:23.884
[mysterious music]

24:23.886 --> 24:25.552
♪ ♪

24:25.554 --> 24:27.053
Whoo.

24:27.055 --> 24:29.389
This guy's got bigger problems
than trespassing.

24:29.391 --> 24:35.295
♪ ♪

24:35.297 --> 24:37.664
Six open warrants
in five states.

24:37.666 --> 24:39.966
Khan's looking at a half-dozen
serious felonies.

24:39.968 --> 24:42.335
Do the charges hold any water?

24:42.337 --> 24:43.503
Yeah, an ocean.

24:43.505 --> 24:45.639
Someone greased the skids
on this guy.

24:45.641 --> 24:47.040
Where did they find a judge
this time of night

24:47.042 --> 24:48.341
to deny him bail?

24:48.343 --> 24:49.876
I'll take it from here then.

24:49.878 --> 24:51.044
[muffled voice in trunk]

24:51.046 --> 24:52.512
What the hell was that?

24:52.514 --> 24:53.880
Plan B.

24:53.882 --> 24:56.416
[banging in trunk]

24:56.418 --> 24:58.485
I got to go back to work.

24:58.487 --> 25:00.320
(man with muffled voice)
Let me out of here!

25:00.322 --> 25:03.356
[door buzzer]

25:03.358 --> 25:07.327
[indistinct background chatter]

25:07.329 --> 25:10.263
[mysterious music]

25:10.265 --> 25:14.301
♪
♪ _

25:14.303 --> 25:17.003
- Fresh meat.
- Looking good.

25:17.005 --> 25:21.207
♪ ♪

25:21.209 --> 25:23.176
(man)
Opening gate!

25:23.178 --> 25:26.313
♪ ♪

25:26.315 --> 25:27.614
(man)
Yeah, check this out.

25:27.616 --> 25:30.517
- Oh, my.
- Ugh.

25:30.519 --> 25:32.285
[gate closes]

25:32.287 --> 25:36.389
♪ ♪

25:36.391 --> 25:39.859
- He's dead.
- Nowhere to run, right?

25:39.861 --> 25:42.663
♪ ♪

25:43.194 --> 25:45.713
_

25:47.669 --> 25:51.004
[phone vibrates]

25:51.006 --> 25:52.853
♪ ♪

25:53.367 --> 25:56.302
_

25:56.912 --> 25:58.378
[phone vibrates]

25:58.921 --> 26:00.423
_

26:00.424 --> 26:02.191
_

26:14.924 --> 26:16.981
_

26:18.133 --> 26:19.566
Samaritan's cut
the security feeds

26:19.568 --> 26:21.601
from the entire cell block.

26:21.603 --> 26:24.070
It doesn't want anyone to see
what's about to happen.

26:24.072 --> 26:25.105
(Finch)
Where are you, Mr. Reese?

26:25.107 --> 26:29.876
♪ ♪

26:29.878 --> 26:32.278
[grunts and gasps]

26:32.280 --> 26:34.881
[gagging]

26:34.883 --> 26:40.620
♪ ♪

26:40.622 --> 26:42.555
[all grunting]

26:42.557 --> 26:45.358
- Whoa! Cool, man.
- Hey, all right.

26:45.360 --> 26:47.694
You've been granted
early release.

26:47.696 --> 26:49.704
♪ ♪

26:50.838 --> 26:52.429
_

26:52.430 --> 26:56.491
_

26:58.139 --> 27:01.021
_

27:01.562 --> 27:03.968
_

27:05.013 --> 27:06.880
I got him.

27:06.882 --> 27:08.481
(Finch) Samaritan is
surely coming for you.

27:08.483 --> 27:09.783
Stick to the shadow map.

27:09.785 --> 27:11.284
This van's a little big
for that,

27:11.286 --> 27:13.319
and half the guards
in Rikers are after us.

27:13.321 --> 27:14.587
I know you.

27:14.589 --> 27:16.890
You were at the bar tonight.

27:16.892 --> 27:17.891
You've been following me.

27:17.893 --> 27:19.059
It sent you to get me.

27:19.061 --> 27:19.993
[tires screeching]

27:19.995 --> 27:26.566
♪ ♪

27:26.568 --> 27:28.068
Hang on.

27:28.070 --> 27:29.736
[Khan shouts]

27:29.738 --> 27:32.272
[horns honking]

27:32.274 --> 27:33.042
♪ ♪

27:33.539 --> 27:35.993
_

27:37.479 --> 27:39.679
[tires screeching]

27:39.681 --> 27:42.849
[metal smashing]

27:48.056 --> 27:49.089
(Finch)
You need to get out of there.

27:49.091 --> 27:50.557
Samaritan's coming.

27:50.559 --> 27:53.493
[suspenseful music]

27:53.495 --> 28:01.768
♪ ♪

28:05.640 --> 28:08.875
Hey, John.
Need a ride?

28:08.877 --> 28:11.711
♪ ♪

28:24.216 --> 28:25.782
Pass the orange chicken.

28:25.784 --> 28:28.718
[mysterious music]

28:28.720 --> 28:31.321
♪ ♪

28:31.323 --> 28:33.723
This mean you've forgiven me,
Harold?

28:33.725 --> 28:38.128
At the moment,
we have more pressing matters.

28:38.130 --> 28:40.830
This safehouse won't stay
that way for long.

28:40.832 --> 28:42.799
He needs to go.

28:42.801 --> 28:46.169
Where does a man hide
when a god wants him dead?

28:46.171 --> 28:48.438
(Reese)
Finch, this guy's brilliant.

28:48.440 --> 28:50.207
Relentless.

28:50.209 --> 28:51.942
Maybe we should just
read him in.

28:51.944 --> 28:53.877
No, he already knows too much.

28:53.879 --> 28:55.979
He's not Simon Lee
or Clair Mahoney.

28:55.981 --> 28:58.415
There's no
convincing him otherwise.

28:58.417 --> 29:01.351
The longer he stays around,
the more questions he'll have.

29:01.353 --> 29:02.953
Want to really blow his mind?

29:02.955 --> 29:06.256
Tell him there are two
of these things.

29:06.258 --> 29:08.959
[gasps]

29:08.961 --> 29:18.902
♪ ♪

29:18.904 --> 29:22.239
Best in the city.

29:22.241 --> 29:23.740
[grunts]

29:23.742 --> 29:27.410
Ah!

29:27.412 --> 29:30.046
They sent you.

29:30.048 --> 29:32.315
They sent you to get me.

29:32.317 --> 29:34.217
Right idea.
Wrong machine.

29:34.219 --> 29:37.554
Not helping, Ms. Groves.

29:37.556 --> 29:38.955
Who are you people?

29:38.957 --> 29:40.824
The only ones keeping you alive.

29:40.826 --> 29:43.927
You almost killed us.

29:43.929 --> 29:45.428
Just a little fender bender.

29:45.430 --> 29:49.099
Answer our questions
and you will be released.

29:49.101 --> 29:52.335
Right.

29:52.337 --> 29:54.671
[Khan grunts]

29:54.673 --> 29:58.842
♪ ♪

29:58.844 --> 30:00.977
Why did you need
to see those meters?

30:00.979 --> 30:02.245
The company was using
ten times the power

30:02.247 --> 30:04.347
than it's ever used before.

30:04.349 --> 30:06.549
It wasn't being used
by the servers inside.

30:06.551 --> 30:08.885
It was powering something else.

30:08.887 --> 30:11.621
It's quite a leap to jump
to an AI.

30:11.623 --> 30:13.857
Stock market flash crash,
cyber attacks,

30:13.859 --> 30:17.027
traffic lights changing
at whim.

30:17.029 --> 30:20.330
That is the work of an invisible
hand that is strangling me.

30:20.332 --> 30:23.667
If you're being targeted,
we need to know why.

30:23.669 --> 30:24.634
My research.

30:24.636 --> 30:25.935
(Finch)
New software?

30:25.937 --> 30:28.038
Bio-tech.
You wouldn't understand.

30:28.040 --> 30:34.077
Try me.
I'm a fast learner.

30:34.079 --> 30:35.912
Digital immunization chip.

30:35.914 --> 30:38.214
We were all ready to go
into production next year.

30:38.216 --> 30:39.983
I think my company was hijacked

30:39.985 --> 30:41.318
so that they could steal
my research

30:41.320 --> 30:44.254
and build the prototype
without me.

30:44.256 --> 30:46.756
(Reese) Finch, remember
that quaint little town

30:46.758 --> 30:49.326
that made transponders?

30:49.328 --> 30:52.228
Could this be
the next generation?

30:52.230 --> 30:54.264
I know
an Artificial Intelligence

30:54.266 --> 30:58.034
is trying to kill me.

30:58.036 --> 31:01.104
I just don't know why.

31:01.106 --> 31:03.173
That's what we're
trying to figure out.

31:03.175 --> 31:07.677
♪ ♪

31:07.679 --> 31:11.381
You believe me.

31:11.383 --> 31:12.849
But you don't work for it?

31:12.851 --> 31:17.454
- [laughs]
- Is that my computer?

31:17.456 --> 31:18.788
Harold.

31:18.790 --> 31:20.757
The port used to hack
Khan's system

31:20.759 --> 31:24.094
sent a small amount of data back
to an off-site IP address.

31:24.096 --> 31:26.796
I was able to determine
its location.

31:26.798 --> 31:32.035
♪ ♪

31:32.037 --> 31:34.671
- What's there?
- Woods.

31:34.673 --> 31:37.707
The trees form a canopy
blocking any overhead images.

31:37.709 --> 31:42.312
♪ ♪

31:42.314 --> 31:45.882
Any idea what else
is out there?

31:45.884 --> 31:48.752
Road trip.

31:50.222 --> 31:53.123
[dramatic music]

31:53.125 --> 31:58.161
♪ ♪

31:58.163 --> 32:01.765
What do you think?
C4 overkill?

32:01.767 --> 32:05.902
Well, better safe than sorry.

32:05.904 --> 32:07.537
Try not to hit any bumps.

32:07.539 --> 32:09.839
(Finch) Mr. Khan, just wait
here and let us handle this.

32:09.841 --> 32:11.608
Please stay inside
as instructed.

32:11.610 --> 32:14.811
I am not gonna wait
for lightning to strike twice.

32:14.813 --> 32:16.479
I need to know why it chose me

32:16.481 --> 32:18.848
because whatever is out there,
it ruined my life.

32:18.850 --> 32:22.485
♪ ♪

32:22.487 --> 32:24.521
[pumps shotgun]

32:24.523 --> 32:25.488
Shotgun.

32:25.490 --> 32:29.759
♪ ♪

32:29.761 --> 32:32.695
[mysterious music]

32:32.697 --> 32:40.970
♪ ♪

32:50.215 --> 32:52.081
We're here.

32:52.083 --> 32:55.051
Are you sure this is the place?

32:55.053 --> 32:57.387
I was expecting something more.

32:57.389 --> 33:00.590
Any idea what your company
would be doing out here?

33:00.592 --> 33:03.026
It's not my company anymore.

33:03.028 --> 33:12.368
♪ ♪

33:12.370 --> 33:14.037
We're sitting ducks out here.

33:14.039 --> 33:17.707
♪ ♪

33:17.709 --> 33:18.975
What is it, Root?

33:18.977 --> 33:20.410
(Root)
My cochlear implant.

33:20.412 --> 33:21.811
I hear something.

33:21.813 --> 33:24.814
Picking up WiFi signals.

33:24.816 --> 33:26.416
Data images.

33:26.418 --> 33:27.450
Where?

33:27.452 --> 33:31.888
Coordinates.
Specific.

33:31.890 --> 33:35.225
Just tell me where to aim.

33:35.227 --> 33:38.461
My 5:00.
250 meters.

33:38.463 --> 33:39.429
[gunshot]

33:39.431 --> 33:41.564
♪ ♪

33:41.566 --> 33:45.168
11:00.
340 meters.

33:45.170 --> 33:47.203
[gunshot]

33:47.204 --> 33:48.701
_

33:48.736 --> 33:49.005
♪ ♪

33:49.007 --> 33:51.040
A matter of minutes
before the cavalry gets here.

33:51.042 --> 33:52.609
(Finch)
Middle of nowhere.

33:52.611 --> 33:55.411
What were those cameras
installed to protect?

33:55.413 --> 33:57.447
♪ ♪

33:57.449 --> 33:59.082
We're in the right place.

33:59.084 --> 34:02.051
(Khan)
What's there?

34:02.053 --> 34:03.887
Not sure.

34:03.889 --> 34:08.024
But we're standing on it.

34:08.025 --> 34:09.826
[grunts]

34:09.828 --> 34:12.728
[dramatic music]

34:12.731 --> 34:19.835
♪ ♪

34:30.507 --> 34:33.442
[suspenseful music]

34:33.444 --> 34:41.717
♪ ♪

35:08.146 --> 35:09.211
(Reese)
Get up.

35:09.213 --> 35:11.180
Whoa, whoa.
Easy, easy.

35:11.182 --> 35:12.181
What is that?

35:12.183 --> 35:13.282
It's diagnostics.

35:13.284 --> 35:15.051
Diagnostics of what?

35:15.053 --> 35:16.452
(man)
Antivirus software.

35:16.454 --> 35:18.187
It's scanning for viruses
all over the grid.

35:18.189 --> 35:20.056
There's a couple hundred
new ones every day.

35:20.058 --> 35:24.627
Samaritan has siphoned off
the resources of your company.

35:24.629 --> 35:26.395
The diesel fuel is being used
to run generators

35:26.397 --> 35:27.897
around the clock.

35:27.899 --> 35:30.700
That is my antivirus software.

35:30.702 --> 35:34.937
All your company's servers
have been hijacked.

35:34.939 --> 35:36.572
Retasked.

35:36.574 --> 35:39.775
It's running a scan
of epic proportions.

35:39.777 --> 35:42.211
A global search.

35:42.213 --> 35:44.647
But the results
were sent out here.

35:44.649 --> 35:46.215
(Khan)
Why?

35:46.217 --> 35:48.818
It's not searching for a virus.

35:48.820 --> 35:52.154
That code.
Do you recognize that?

35:52.156 --> 35:56.392
We need to leave.
Now.

35:56.394 --> 35:57.460
Is there another exit?

35:57.462 --> 35:59.862
No.
One way in, one way out.

35:59.864 --> 36:01.297
Finch?

36:01.299 --> 36:03.599
Take it.

36:03.601 --> 36:06.602
Then you stay close.

36:06.604 --> 36:09.705
What is that?
Hey!

36:09.707 --> 36:17.980
♪ ♪

36:21.452 --> 36:24.453
[gunfire]

36:24.455 --> 36:27.390
[tense music]

36:27.392 --> 36:31.193
♪ ♪

36:31.195 --> 36:32.094
[grunts]

36:32.096 --> 36:33.929
♪ ♪

36:33.931 --> 36:37.299
That was my software!
That was my software!

36:37.301 --> 36:39.201
Yeah, but it's elevated.

36:39.203 --> 36:40.102
And then some.

36:40.104 --> 36:42.905
♪ ♪

36:42.907 --> 36:44.407
We should hang back.

36:44.409 --> 36:46.942
Draw them out.

36:46.944 --> 36:47.977
(Root)
It's Martine.

36:47.979 --> 36:51.313
♪ ♪

36:51.315 --> 36:53.349
Sorry, John.

36:53.351 --> 36:55.084
Places to be, people to kill.

36:55.086 --> 36:58.187
- Damn it, Root.
- [grunts]

36:58.189 --> 37:00.623
That was the work of an
Artificial Intelligence!

37:00.625 --> 37:02.291
What does it do?
Who built it?

37:02.293 --> 37:03.626
What is--
Does it see the future?

37:03.628 --> 37:04.994
Does it--
How does it function?

37:04.996 --> 37:06.362
Tell me!
You have the answers!

37:06.364 --> 37:08.764
[gunfire]

37:08.766 --> 37:10.800
- Reese!
- [grunts]

37:10.802 --> 37:11.734
[gunshot]

37:11.736 --> 37:15.171
♪ ♪

37:15.173 --> 37:16.505
[grunts]

37:16.507 --> 37:19.408
[guns clicking]

37:19.410 --> 37:22.445
♪ ♪

37:22.447 --> 37:25.347
[both grunting]

37:25.349 --> 37:33.622
♪ ♪

37:37.328 --> 37:39.028
I liked you better as a blond.

37:39.030 --> 37:40.262
[both grunting]

37:40.264 --> 37:42.431
I need to know
what this thing is.

37:42.433 --> 37:44.233
It destroyed my life.

37:44.235 --> 37:47.703
Yours is not the first life
it's ruined.

37:47.705 --> 37:49.672
- [gunshot]
- Ah!

37:49.674 --> 37:53.442
♪ ♪

37:53.444 --> 37:54.610
Where's Khan?

37:54.612 --> 37:59.348
♪ ♪

37:59.350 --> 38:01.951
It's seems my answers
were unsatisfactory.

38:01.953 --> 38:07.223
♪ ♪

38:07.225 --> 38:11.060
[both grunting]

38:11.062 --> 38:12.561
They're coming!

38:12.563 --> 38:15.164
I'm gonna kill her!

38:22.206 --> 38:25.141
[solemn music]

38:25.143 --> 38:27.610
♪ ♪

38:27.612 --> 38:29.311
No need to thank me.

38:29.313 --> 38:31.814
You should have let me
kill her.

38:31.816 --> 38:34.583
It won't bring Shaw back.

38:34.585 --> 38:38.554
♪ ♪

38:38.556 --> 38:40.556
You're right.
I should have let you kill her.

38:40.558 --> 38:43.826
♪ ♪

38:43.828 --> 38:45.427
That's a nice case.

38:45.429 --> 38:49.031
♪ ♪

38:49.033 --> 38:50.466
Custom made.

38:50.468 --> 38:54.503
Some kind of carbon fiber
Kevlar weave.

38:54.505 --> 38:57.106
What's inside it?

38:57.108 --> 38:58.974
She hasn't told me yet.

38:58.976 --> 39:01.110
Well, get some rest.

39:01.112 --> 39:02.444
We need you ready for battle.

39:02.446 --> 39:06.549
♪ ♪

39:06.551 --> 39:09.451
[phone vibrates]

39:09.453 --> 39:12.188
♪ ♪

39:12.190 --> 39:15.825
[mysterious music]

39:15.827 --> 39:17.126
[chuckles]

39:17.128 --> 39:25.401
♪ ♪

39:31.275 --> 39:34.777
You sure?

39:34.779 --> 39:36.278
Hmm.

39:36.280 --> 39:38.314
Seems like a waste.

39:38.316 --> 39:40.950
[glass shatters]

39:40.952 --> 39:42.585
That's why you're the boss.

39:42.587 --> 39:51.060
♪ ♪

39:51.062 --> 39:54.196
Still no sign of Khan.

39:54.198 --> 39:56.332
Hopefully he's safe,

39:56.334 --> 39:59.335
sitting on a beach somewhere.

39:59.337 --> 40:03.072
Khan went searching for answers
that you wouldn't provide.

40:03.074 --> 40:04.907
What did he see down there,
Finch?

40:04.909 --> 40:07.943
My own creation.

40:07.945 --> 40:10.479
When I built the Machine,
I didn't use any existing

40:10.481 --> 40:13.349
operating system or language.

40:13.351 --> 40:16.185
Code was one of a kind.

40:16.187 --> 40:18.621
Samaritan knew that.

40:18.623 --> 40:21.891
So if Samaritan started a search
for unrecognizable code

40:21.893 --> 40:24.760
using traditional means,

40:24.762 --> 40:28.097
the Machine would have been
alerted instantly.

40:28.099 --> 40:31.600
So Samaritan found something
that the Machine

40:31.602 --> 40:33.969
would never detect.

40:33.971 --> 40:37.206
Khan's software.

40:37.208 --> 40:40.376
Installed in every
network device.

40:40.378 --> 40:42.611
Means and an access
already in place.

40:42.613 --> 40:45.114
It was a brilliant stratagem,
really.

40:45.116 --> 40:47.182
This program,
running in the background

40:47.184 --> 40:51.320
of your computer,
checking every file.

40:51.322 --> 40:54.356
But instead of viruses,
Samaritan was using it

40:54.358 --> 40:56.392
to search for the Machine.

40:56.394 --> 40:59.228
Did it find
the Machine's location?

40:59.230 --> 41:02.097
It's only a matter of time.

41:02.099 --> 41:05.501
[pay phone ringing]

41:05.503 --> 41:11.340
♪ ♪

41:14.178 --> 41:17.079
[ominous music]

41:17.081 --> 41:25.254
♪ ♪

41:25.256 --> 41:27.823
It's a pleasure to finally
meet you, Mr. Khan.

41:27.825 --> 41:31.327
Sorry we had to resort
to rather drastic measures,

41:31.329 --> 41:34.763
but you've been
awfully persistent.

41:34.765 --> 41:36.332
Who are you?

41:36.334 --> 41:40.102
A man who knows the answers.

41:40.104 --> 41:41.603
Why me?

41:41.605 --> 41:45.941
Your antivirus software
helped me search the grid

41:45.943 --> 41:49.979
to finally track down
their Machine once and for all.

41:49.981 --> 41:54.283
Unfortunately, it determined
it's not on any network devices

41:54.285 --> 41:55.517
in the world.

41:55.519 --> 41:57.353
Machine?
What?

41:57.355 --> 42:00.422
An Artificial Intelligence.

42:00.424 --> 42:02.291
A god.

42:02.293 --> 42:06.562
One of the two among us.

42:06.564 --> 42:11.033
I knew it.

42:11.035 --> 42:12.401
Is that it?

42:12.403 --> 42:15.571
This is merely the mountaintop.

42:15.573 --> 42:18.140
Does that answer
all your questions?

42:18.142 --> 42:21.010
I want to see it.

42:21.012 --> 42:23.879
I want to look in its eyes.

42:23.881 --> 42:26.048
Very well.

42:26.050 --> 42:27.082
[gunshot]

42:27.084 --> 42:28.317
[grunts]

42:28.319 --> 42:30.589
♪ ♪

42:35.840 --> 42:40.411
_

